.TH "input_set_keycode" 9 "input_set_keycode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
input_set_keycode \- attribute a keycode to a given scancode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" input_set_keycode
.BI "(struct input_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct input_keymap_entry *ke "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
input device which keymap is being updated
.IP "ke" 12
new keymap entry
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should be called by anyone needing to update current
keymap. Presently keyboard and evdev handlers use it.
